Overview

StockTrack is a full-featured online store designed for selling computer parts. It supports role-based access control, giving different interfaces and permissions to regular users and admins. The application is containerized with Docker for cloud deployment and scalability.

Features
  Browse and purchase computer parts as a regular user
  Admin dashboard for managing inventory and users
  Role-based access (User vs Admin views and permissions)
  Dockerized for easy deployment
  Web-based interface running on localhost:8080

Tech Stack
  Java
  Spring Boot
  HTML
  SQL
  Docker
  IntelliJ IDEA (for development and testing)

Getting Started
Requirements:

  Java 17
  Docker (optional, for containerized deployment)
  IntelliJ IDEA (or another IDE)

Running Locally

  Clone the repository
  Open the project in IntelliJ
  Run the application
  Visit: http://localhost:8080/

Login Credentials:
  Role	  Username	  Password
  User	  User	      User123
  Admin	  admin	      Admin123

Docker Deployment (Optional)

  docker build -t stocktrack .
  docker run -p 8080:8080 stocktrack

Then access it at http://localhost:8080/

Author: Jeffrey VanMeter

Notes

